      "This query `r.table('smalldoc').filter(r.row.hasFields('non_existent'))` or this query `r.table('smalldoc').withFields('non_existent')` consume approximately 100 MB each time I run them, which is never freed as far as I can tell. If I run them multiple times the memory usage just stacks up.\r\n\r\nOther filters such as `r.table('smalldoc').filter(r.row('id').eq('non_existent'))` are fine.\r\n\r\nThat looks like a serious memory leak.\r\nLet me see what Valgrind has to say about this..."
